      • timeRatio

        public float timeRatio()
        The ratio between the time delta's. It should show how much tempo of the song was changed, using a percentage. The resolution is 2%. E.g. 110% tells you that query was 10% faster than the reference track.
        Returns:
        The time ratio.

      • frequencyRatio

        public int frequencyRatio()
        The ratio between the reference and query frequency.
        Returns:
        A ratio that tells how much the query frequency is scaled compared to the reference. E.g. 118% translates to +300 cents.
